/*
:name: dyn_tuple_mut_ro
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: dyn_tuple_mut_ro.msel
:pyrope_top: dyn_tuple_mut_ro.msel
*/

// A read-only `mut` (non-array-typed) tuple of constants is also a muxable
// value: with no indexed write its slot trivials are exact, so a runtime index
// lowers to the balanced Hotmux. (A runtime-indexed WRITE to a non-array tuple
// has no hardware lowering and errors at the store, so an all-constant tuple
// reaching the dynamic-index lowering cannot be hiding a dropped write.) A
// runtime-indexed `mut` *array* (`mut t:[4]u8`) still becomes a Memory cell —
// see mem_mut_array.
comb msel(sel:u2) -> (z:u8) {
  mut choices = (5, 6, 7, 8)
  z = choices[sel]
}
